article.headline: Long Beach State 73, CS Bakersfield 70
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. (AP) -- Aaron Nixon scored a career-high 22 points and Sterling Byrd added 15 points as Long Beach State beat Cal State Bakersfield 73-70 Friday night. The 49ers opened the second half with a 15-7 run to take a 45-37 lead with 13:51 remaining and never relinquished the lead. Richard Andrews' lay-up with 14.2 seconds left in the game trimmed the Long Beach State lead to 70-67. Kejuan Johnson then made one of two free throws to give the 49ers a 71-67 lead with 12 seconds left. Byrd stole a pass with 5.8 left and made two free throws to seal the game for Long Beach State. Johnson scored 13 points for the 49ers (2-1), who were out-rebounded 58-44. Bakersfield's Carl Damus scored a career-high 24 points and 12 rebounds for his first career double-double. Dwan Rice scored 13 points and Andrews had 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Roadrunners (0-2). Nixon's basket with 7:30 left in the first half gave the 49ers a 28-12 lead. Cal State Bakersfield then went on an 18-2 run for the remainder of the half and held Long Beach State without a basket. Hall's dunk at the buzzer tied the game 30-30 at halftime.
